<li><a href="http://www.30000khz.com" class="external text" title="http://www.30000khz.com" rel="nofollow">30,000 Kilohertz of Sound</a> Theatrical production that incorporates shortwave broadcasts.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.earstoourworld.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.earstoourworld.org/" rel="nofollow">Ears To Our World</a> is a shortwave radio distribution project for classrooms in the developing world.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.economist.com/world/international/displaystory.cfm?story_id=11590746&amp;fsrc=RSS" class="external text" title="http://www.economist.com/world/international/displaystory.cfm?story_id=11590746&amp;fsrc=RSS" rel="nofollow">Article in the News by the Economist.</a> Describing pros and cons of short wave radio, since the <a href="/wiki/Cold_War" title="Cold War">Cold War</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://wap.hfradio.org/" class="external text" title="http://wap.hfradio.org/" rel="nofollow">WAP/WML SWL Resources</a>, a searchable database of international shortwave broadcasting stations by frequency, intended for mobile devices capable of displaying <a href="/wiki/Wireless_Markup_Language" title="Wireless Markup Language">Wireless Markup Language</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Wireless_Application_Protocol" title="Wireless Application Protocol">Wireless Application Protocol</a></li>
<li><a href="http://home.earthlink.net/~haggisizing/srw-swl/swl-audio.htm" class="external text" title="http://home.earthlink.net/~haggisizing/srw-swl/swl-audio.htm" rel="nofollow">Optimizing Your SWL'ing Audio Experience.</a> Hints for improving reception.</li>
</ul>
